<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFB8FFE26DC2FBE2FBA5AFB1" pageId="28" pageNumber="1541" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFB8FFE26DC2FBE2FBA5AFB1" blockId="28.[178,1085,1151,1203]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1541">
Diagnosis: This is the only member of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFB8FFE26FFCFBE2FC85AF96" authorityName="CHEVROLAT. Part" authorityYear="1834" box="[652,784,1151,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Platynoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFB8FFE26FFCFBE2FC85AF96" box="[652,784,1151,1172]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1541">Platynoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whose elytral disc is entirely or almost entirely black; there may be a faintly visible pale spot at the center of the disc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFB8FFE26DC2FB5FFE47AD07" pageId="28" pageNumber="1541" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFB8FFE26DC2FB5FFE5EAEC0" blockId="28.[178,1086,1218,1474]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1541">
Description: Size: Length 16.0 mm; width 8.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFB8FFE26EEAFB5FFC67AFDA" box="[922,1010,1218,1240]" captionStart="Figs 165-168" captionStartId="53.[178,218,1515,1537]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-59@53.[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figs 165-168: Habitus illustrations of (165) Platynoptera humeralis, holotype; (166) P. lyciformis, lectotype; (167) P. ampliata, non-type; (168) P. ochreata, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282523/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1541">Fig. 167</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium black, vertex with narrow flavotestaceous streak, labrum flavotestaceous; pronotum bicolorous, sides and front flavotestaceous, disc black; elytra mostly black, with two faintly visible maculae at the middle of disc. Head: Antennal capitulum long, each capitular antennomere longer than combined length of funicular antennomeres; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 45/45. Thorax: Pronotum quadrate, flared at sides, anterior margin projected at middle, side margin of disc rounded; PW/PL 160/160; elytra strongly flared at sides, disc with 4 carina; EL/EW 780/220. Abdomen: Female pygidium not incised at distal margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFB8FFE26DC2FA4CFE47AD07" blockId="28.[178,1085,1489,1541]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1541">
Variation: Size: length 12.0-16.0 mm; width 6.0-8.0 mm. In 
<specimenCount id="42C3C782FFB8FFE26EF5FA4FFB86AEE5" box="[901,1043,1489,1511]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1541" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
the elytral disc is entirely black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
